The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                The BA and BSc Part III (general) examinations of Calcutta University under the 1+1+1 pattern will start on May 20 instead of May 4. The BCom Part III (general) exams under the 1+1+1 system will begin on May 21 instead of May 5. The exam schedule has been revised because of the Lok Sabha polls. The detailed revised schedule will be announced later, a university official said on Friday.    Three trains  the New Delhi-Bilaspur-Howrah Rajdhani Express, Howrah-Vasco Amaravati Express and the Purulia-Howrah Rupasi Bangla Express  will arrive at and depart from the old complex of Howrah station for 25 days from March 22 because of repairs on platform 21 of the new complex, the Eastern Railway said on Friday.    A man in his 50s died after falling off the roof of a two-storey building in Khardah where he lived on Thursday night. Tridib Roy Burman was admitted to a private hospital off the Bypass with multiple injuries. He died early on Friday. Police said Roy Burman was suffering from depression. The body has been sent for post-mortem.    Six armed men looted around Rs 1 lakh from a petrol pump in Sonarpur on Friday. Police said the criminals came on two motorcycles and snatched the money at gunpoint. The cleaners of two trucks were beaten up when they tried to stop the goons.    The E block of Writers Buildings, close to chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjees office, went without power for a few minutes around 2.50pm on Friday. The chief minister and his colleagues were in the Assembly. An official said the power failure was caused by a mechanical fault.    A 23-year-old woman was seriously injured after being hit by a speeding private bus on route 41A near the JL Nehru Road-Park Street crossing on Friday. Police said Jyoti Parmer, a resident Regent Park, was taken to SSKM Hospital around 8.20am. The driver fled with the bus.    Three persons involved in a series of robberies on local trains and in a jewellery shop in the city were arrested in Nadia and Barrackpore on Friday, police said.            
